stylometry:
The tradeoff of when you decide to place an order is how long you have for the order to get there, how much to order, how much are your costs of the order. 

Safety Stock is not the MD+ZSTD like I had said in the previous problem. SS is the z-score times the standard deviation. The ROP (re order points) of a company is MD+ZSTD. You must look at how many time you have for the order to come in. You must ensure that you have enough safety stock to get you through until the time the order comes in. You must also decide how much to order. When to order is decided by your ROP or re order points. This shows you that when your inventory numbers get to your ROP to maintain your service level that you have set for your company you must re order your product.
